              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/659fa1fe-d673-4529-b40a-2af2df2d04cd/hikerwise-com-Fho4oV1_VQY-unsplash.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1920x1280" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/659fa1fe-d673-4529-b40a-2af2df2d04cd/hikerwise-com-Fho4oV1_VQY-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w" width="1920" height="1280" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/659fa1fe-d673-4529-b40a-2af2df2d04cd/hikerwise-com-Fho4oV1_VQY-unsplash.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/659fa1fe-d673-4529-b40a-2af2df2d04cd/hikerwise-com-Fho4oV1_VQY-unsplash.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/659fa1fe-d673-4529-b40a-2af2df2d04cd/hikerwise-com-Fho4oV1_VQY-unsplash.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/659fa1fe-d673-4529-b40a-2af2df2d04cd/hikerwise-com-Fho4oV1_VQY-unsplash.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/659fa1fe-d673-4529-b40a-2af2df2d04cd/hikerwise-com-Fho4oV1_VQY-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/659fa1fe-d673-4529-b40a-2af2df2d04cd/hikerwise-com-Fho4oV1_VQY-unsplash.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/659fa1fe-d673-4529-b40a-2af2df2d04cd/hikerwise-com-Fho4oV1_VQY-unsplash.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class="">Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@hikerwise?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Hikerwise.com</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/a-man-with-a-backpack-on-top-of-a-mountain-Fho4oV1_VQY?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">I remember, on my travels, how much fun it was to explore the world, visit countries &amp; cities I’d never been to before, meet new people, and to grow as a human being.&nbsp;</p><p class="">I also recall how tiring it was to make decisions every single day, be it about what to eat, what to see, where to go, what to explore next, what train to catch and when - or whether I should take an Uber? -, what hostels to stay at or whether I should splurge on Airbnbs, what tickets I should buy for what museums / churches / castles / galleries / events and for what price, what destinations I would visit next, and so on and so forth - you get the gist.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Despite the benefits and adventurousness of backpacking, let’s be honest, it can be hard stuff.&nbsp;</p><p class="">So I came up with a list of tips to help <em>you</em> pace your journey, and avoid burnout whilst traveling.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Here they are:&nbsp;</p><h1>TABLE OF CONTENTS:</h1><ol data-rte-list="default"><li><h2><a href="#point-one-rest" target="_blank">Get plenty of rest &amp; sleep.&nbsp;</a></h2></li><li><h2><a href="#point-two-plan-in-advance" target="_blank">Plan as much as you can in advance.&nbsp;</a></h2></li><li><h2><a href="#point-three-do-nothing-chill" target="_blank">Make room during your days to do nothing and relax / chill / be spontaneous.&nbsp;</a></h2></li></ol>





















  
  






  <h3>1. Get plenty of rest &amp; sleep.&nbsp;</h3>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/47354158-f242-43b2-b948-bcffb67e7926/kalegin-ffustAcaX0E-unsplash.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1920x1280" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/47354158-f242-43b2-b948-bcffb67e7926/kalegin-ffustAcaX0E-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w" width="1920" height="1280" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/47354158-f242-43b2-b948-bcffb67e7926/kalegin-ffustAcaX0E-unsplash.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/47354158-f242-43b2-b948-bcffb67e7926/kalegin-ffustAcaX0E-unsplash.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/47354158-f242-43b2-b948-bcffb67e7926/kalegin-ffustAcaX0E-unsplash.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/47354158-f242-43b2-b948-bcffb67e7926/kalegin-ffustAcaX0E-unsplash.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/47354158-f242-43b2-b948-bcffb67e7926/kalegin-ffustAcaX0E-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/47354158-f242-43b2-b948-bcffb67e7926/kalegin-ffustAcaX0E-unsplash.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/47354158-f242-43b2-b948-bcffb67e7926/kalegin-ffustAcaX0E-unsplash.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class="">Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@kalegin?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Михаил Калегин</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/woman-sleeping-on-trailer-ffustAcaX0E?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">Let’s face it: when you’re globetrotting, you’re likely not always getting the amount of rest you need. Because between train rides, jumping from city to city &amp; country to country, and waking up early to explore or make your booked time slots at museums / galleries / castles / exhibitions / tours - whatever -, you’re probably constantly setting the alarm clock to wake up at a certain time. Not to mention that you’re probably staying out late partying with your hostel mates or just exploring.&nbsp;</p><p class="">While it’s inevitable that on some nights you’re going to lose sleep, in the long run, you want to make it a priority to get enough rest. If that means catching up on sleep during long train rides between cities and countries, go for it - I had some of my best sleeps on train rides… just be careful that nobody steals your backpack like mine got stolen if you’re not in individual compartments. If it means sleeping in on some days, go for it. At the end of the day, you can always extend your stay by a day or two - or however long you want, really - in certain countries / cities if you really like it there. Bottom line is this: if you don’t get enough rest, you’re going to get tired. If you get tired, you’re not going to have fun, and you’ll want to end your trip early. So make sure to sleep adequately and recharge your batteries. Rest is crucial to having a good time and making your backpacking trip sustainable.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>





















  
  






  <h3>2. Plan as much as you can in advance.&nbsp;</h3>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/24c7478f-3460-46b4-908f-6d3b69ff0439/glenn-carstens-peters-RLw-UC03Gwc-unsplash.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1920x1278" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/24c7478f-3460-46b4-908f-6d3b69ff0439/glenn-carstens-peters-RLw-UC03Gwc-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w" width="1920" height="1278" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/24c7478f-3460-46b4-908f-6d3b69ff0439/glenn-carstens-peters-RLw-UC03Gwc-unsplash.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/24c7478f-3460-46b4-908f-6d3b69ff0439/glenn-carstens-peters-RLw-UC03Gwc-unsplash.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/24c7478f-3460-46b4-908f-6d3b69ff0439/glenn-carstens-peters-RLw-UC03Gwc-unsplash.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/24c7478f-3460-46b4-908f-6d3b69ff0439/glenn-carstens-peters-RLw-UC03Gwc-unsplash.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/24c7478f-3460-46b4-908f-6d3b69ff0439/glenn-carstens-peters-RLw-UC03Gwc-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/24c7478f-3460-46b4-908f-6d3b69ff0439/glenn-carstens-peters-RLw-UC03Gwc-unsplash.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/24c7478f-3460-46b4-908f-6d3b69ff0439/glenn-carstens-peters-RLw-UC03Gwc-unsplash.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class="">Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@glenncarstenspeters?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Glenn Carstens-Peters</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/person-writing-bucket-list-on-book-RLw-UC03Gwc?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">One of the reasons that burnout happens is because of decision fatigue. This is incredibly common among backpackers because you’re constantly deciding what to do / where to go / what to see next, what countries or cities to visit, what modes of transportation to take, what sort of accommodations to book, etc.&nbsp;</p><p class="">To avoid decision fatigue, I recommend pre-planning as much of your trip as possible. Okay, now let’s be honest: you’re likely not going to plan a lot of your trip in advance because you want to be spontaneous and adventurous. I totally agree; I’m like that as well. That said, if you could even just figure out one to three places that you absolutely want to visit in each of the cities that you plan to go to, it’ll help out a lot. Likewise, it’s sometimes even advisable to get tickets in advance to certain flights, destinations, or even exhibitions - a. To avoid lineups or sold out tickets, and b. To avoid needing to make <em>more</em> decisions than you already have to make. If you know in advance that you’re scheduled to be somewhere at a certain date and time, it liberates you from having to decide on the day of what you’re going to do that day. Again, I’m not suggesting to avoid spontaneity, as that’s obviously the fun part. I’m just saying to free up your brain a little bit.&nbsp;</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/35c81a85-3d13-4b70-8447-0f46400b0f39/chris-lawton-duQ1ulzTJbM-unsplash.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1920x1307" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/35c81a85-3d13-4b70-8447-0f46400b0f39/chris-lawton-duQ1ulzTJbM-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w" width="1920" height="1307" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/35c81a85-3d13-4b70-8447-0f46400b0f39/chris-lawton-duQ1ulzTJbM-unsplash.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/35c81a85-3d13-4b70-8447-0f46400b0f39/chris-lawton-duQ1ulzTJbM-unsplash.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/35c81a85-3d13-4b70-8447-0f46400b0f39/chris-lawton-duQ1ulzTJbM-unsplash.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/35c81a85-3d13-4b70-8447-0f46400b0f39/chris-lawton-duQ1ulzTJbM-unsplash.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/35c81a85-3d13-4b70-8447-0f46400b0f39/chris-lawton-duQ1ulzTJbM-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/35c81a85-3d13-4b70-8447-0f46400b0f39/chris-lawton-duQ1ulzTJbM-unsplash.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/35c81a85-3d13-4b70-8447-0f46400b0f39/chris-lawton-duQ1ulzTJbM-unsplash.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class="">Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@chrislawton?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Chris Lawton</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/black-and-silver-slr-camera-on-table-duQ1ulzTJbM?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">An alternative to having everything planned out is to have dedicated resources that you go to for advice on what to do in each city or country. Examples include our blog, <a href="http://resilienceroutes.com"><span>resilienceroutes.com</span></a>, or a Youtube channel that I used throughout my backpacking travels called <a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/woltersworld"><span>Wolter’s World</span></a> - he’s incredibly helpful, and a joy to watch. I used his tips on where to travel, what to see, and what to eat on pretty much my entire journey, and I loved it. Whatever resources you choose, it’s another go-to supply of information that you don’t need to make a choice about - because you already trust them. And that frees up your brain from decision fatigue and burnout.&nbsp;</p>





















  
  






  <h3>3. Make room during your days to do nothing and relax / chill / be spontaneous.&nbsp;</h3>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/52f83b40-9ea4-4515-a443-2355093fe0b8/robson-hatsukami-morgan-r8hw4Zs38zo-unsplash.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1920x1280" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/52f83b40-9ea4-4515-a443-2355093fe0b8/robson-hatsukami-morgan-r8hw4Zs38zo-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w" width="1920" height="1280" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/52f83b40-9ea4-4515-a443-2355093fe0b8/robson-hatsukami-morgan-r8hw4Zs38zo-unsplash.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/52f83b40-9ea4-4515-a443-2355093fe0b8/robson-hatsukami-morgan-r8hw4Zs38zo-unsplash.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/52f83b40-9ea4-4515-a443-2355093fe0b8/robson-hatsukami-morgan-r8hw4Zs38zo-unsplash.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/52f83b40-9ea4-4515-a443-2355093fe0b8/robson-hatsukami-morgan-r8hw4Zs38zo-unsplash.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/52f83b40-9ea4-4515-a443-2355093fe0b8/robson-hatsukami-morgan-r8hw4Zs38zo-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/52f83b40-9ea4-4515-a443-2355093fe0b8/robson-hatsukami-morgan-r8hw4Zs38zo-unsplash.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/52f83b40-9ea4-4515-a443-2355093fe0b8/robson-hatsukami-morgan-r8hw4Zs38zo-unsplash.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class="">Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@robsonhmorgan?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Robson Hatsukami Morgan</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/man-swimming-in-spring-r8hw4Zs38zo?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">And finally, take breaks. Yes, you’re going to want to see as much as you can in the short amount of time you spend in each city you visit. And just make sure to pace yourself. Take time to actually enjoy and experience each destination - not just the countries and cities, but also the museums, monuments, tours, churches, castles, and whatever else you might go and experience.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Remember: you don’t have to see <em>everything</em> - as tempting as it is. You just want to see the important stuff.&nbsp;</p><p class="">And this - hopefully - won’t be your last time visiting any of these places. It’s just an introduction.&nbsp;</p><p class="">So take it easy, avoid trying to squeeze in everything, and focus on the <span><strong>quality</strong></span> of your journey rather than the <span><strong>quantity</strong></span> of the places you visit and sites you see.&nbsp;</p><p class="">In the long run, that’ll make for a more enjoyable and memorable experience that’ll motivate you to go backpacking again.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Thanks for visiting / reading. We hope you gained value from our post. If you enjoyed these tips, consider subscribing to our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/people/Resilience-Routes/61551906447595/"><span>Facebook</span></a>, <a href="https://x.com/R_Routes"><span>Twitter / X</span></a>, and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/resilienceroutes/?next=%2F"><span>Instagram</span></a> pages to receive weekly backpacking &amp; travel advice.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Until next time, stay <strong>resilient</strong> out there.&nbsp;</p>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title>Wander Wisely: Budget-Friendly Adventures in Budapest</title><dc:creator>Michael Boroda</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 06 Aug 2024 22:47:40 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.resilienceroutes.com/blog/wander-wisely-budget-friendly-adventures-in-budapest</link><guid isPermaLink="false">64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588:64fce74e086c7e17fabddba4:66b29c77fb823f73847494b5</guid><description><![CDATA[Are you still struggling to find things to do in Budapest, despite reading 
our last article? 

Are you scared that the Pearl of the Danube is too expensive for you to 
enjoy on a budget? 

Then read on…]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/4ed0ca69-045c-400d-a9c1-63e75471006a/emma-fabbri-2TmsyZXMNTE-unsplash.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1920x1280" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/4ed0ca69-045c-400d-a9c1-63e75471006a/emma-fabbri-2TmsyZXMNTE-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w" width="1920" height="1280" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/4ed0ca69-045c-400d-a9c1-63e75471006a/emma-fabbri-2TmsyZXMNTE-unsplash.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/4ed0ca69-045c-400d-a9c1-63e75471006a/emma-fabbri-2TmsyZXMNTE-unsplash.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/4ed0ca69-045c-400d-a9c1-63e75471006a/emma-fabbri-2TmsyZXMNTE-unsplash.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/4ed0ca69-045c-400d-a9c1-63e75471006a/emma-fabbri-2TmsyZXMNTE-unsplash.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/4ed0ca69-045c-400d-a9c1-63e75471006a/emma-fabbri-2TmsyZXMNTE-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/4ed0ca69-045c-400d-a9c1-63e75471006a/emma-fabbri-2TmsyZXMNTE-unsplash.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/4ed0ca69-045c-400d-a9c1-63e75471006a/emma-fabbri-2TmsyZXMNTE-unsplash.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class="">Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@fabevent?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Emma Fabbri</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/fishermans-bastion-in-budapest-during-daytime-2TmsyZXMNTE?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">What’s up, backpackers?&nbsp;</p><p class="">Are you still struggling to find things to do in Budapest, despite reading our <a href="https://www.resilienceroutes.com/blog/the-frugal-travelers-guide-to-budapest-must-see-sights-and-experiences"><span>last article</span></a>?&nbsp;</p><p class="">Are you scared that the Pearl of the Danube is too expensive for you to enjoy on a budget?&nbsp;</p><p class="">Quit worrying. I’ve got you covered with three more, budget-friendly tourist activities in Budapest. And these are just the tip of the iceberg!&nbsp;</p><p class="">Let’s get started anyway.&nbsp;</p><h3>TABLE OF CONTENTS:&nbsp;</h3><ol data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><a href="#point-one-margaret-island" target="_blank">Island Escapes: Affordable Fun in Budapest's Margaret Island</a></p></li><li><p class=""><a href="#point-two-ruin-bars" target="_blank">Ruin Bar Revelry: Affordable Nights Out in Budapest </a></p></li><li><p class=""><a href="#point-three-great-market-hall" target="_blank">Bargain Bites: Discovering the Great Market Hall's Affordable Delights </a></p></li></ol>





















  
  






  <ol data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="">Explore Margaret Island</p></li></ol>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/2961601d-ef94-4d94-a1e3-39de2da5c936/linda-gerbec-_DikUgCRa90-unsplash.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1920x1440" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/2961601d-ef94-4d94-a1e3-39de2da5c936/linda-gerbec-_DikUgCRa90-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w" width="1920" height="1440" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/2961601d-ef94-4d94-a1e3-39de2da5c936/linda-gerbec-_DikUgCRa90-unsplash.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/2961601d-ef94-4d94-a1e3-39de2da5c936/linda-gerbec-_DikUgCRa90-unsplash.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/2961601d-ef94-4d94-a1e3-39de2da5c936/linda-gerbec-_DikUgCRa90-unsplash.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/2961601d-ef94-4d94-a1e3-39de2da5c936/linda-gerbec-_DikUgCRa90-unsplash.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/2961601d-ef94-4d94-a1e3-39de2da5c936/linda-gerbec-_DikUgCRa90-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/2961601d-ef94-4d94-a1e3-39de2da5c936/linda-gerbec-_DikUgCRa90-unsplash.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/2961601d-ef94-4d94-a1e3-39de2da5c936/linda-gerbec-_DikUgCRa90-unsplash.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class="">Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@lsgerbec?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Linda Gerbec</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/green-trees-near-white-concrete-building-during-daytime-_DikUgCRa90?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">Margaret Island, located in the middle of the Danube River, offers you an escape from the city's noise and bustle. It's a perfect spot because entry is free, and there are plenty of affordable activities to enjoy, such as <a href="https://gomobility.eu/?lang=en"><span>renting a bike</span></a>, visiting the <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=margaret+island+budapest+musical+fountain&amp;sca_esv=0e526ec8824269be&amp;rlz=1C5CHFA_enCA861CA861&amp;sxsrf=ADLYWIJiT35W0Eszy9Ga6a50hCi5KU196A%3A1722924856237&amp;ei=OL-xZuybDuj_ptQP0KnyuQM&amp;oq=margaret+island+budapest+musical&amp;gs_&amp;sclient=gws-wiz-serp"><span>musical fountain</span></a>, or hiking through the beautiful gardens.</p><p class="">In addition to the walkways, there are plenty of other things to see on this island. You can navigate around parkland and greenery. You can also see an art nouveau water tower, the ruins of a 13th-century Dominican convent, and a small zoo. Other attractions include jogging tracks, <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=margaret+island+thermal+spa+budapest&amp;sca_esv=0e526ec8824269be&amp;rlz=1C5CHFA_enCA861CA861&amp;sxsrf=ADLYWILNdSuyeVQibZZXYdnynW_TRyUlJg%3A1722924989325&amp;ei=vb-xZofLE-iJptQPk97D-Qs&amp;oq=margaret+island+thermal+sp&amp;gs_&amp;sclient=gws-wiz-serp"><span>thermal spas and swimming pools</span></a>. Summertime brings pop-up bars and restaurants, as well as live music</p>





















  
  






  <p class="">2. Discover Budapest's Ruin Bars</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/dfefa37c-e64f-4ef5-895c-e7f0e62d6814/nick-night-RrOtl3HSP80-unsplash.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1920x1280" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/dfefa37c-e64f-4ef5-895c-e7f0e62d6814/nick-night-RrOtl3HSP80-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w" width="1920" height="1280" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/dfefa37c-e64f-4ef5-895c-e7f0e62d6814/nick-night-RrOtl3HSP80-unsplash.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/dfefa37c-e64f-4ef5-895c-e7f0e62d6814/nick-night-RrOtl3HSP80-unsplash.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/dfefa37c-e64f-4ef5-895c-e7f0e62d6814/nick-night-RrOtl3HSP80-unsplash.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/dfefa37c-e64f-4ef5-895c-e7f0e62d6814/nick-night-RrOtl3HSP80-unsplash.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/dfefa37c-e64f-4ef5-895c-e7f0e62d6814/nick-night-RrOtl3HSP80-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/dfefa37c-e64f-4ef5-895c-e7f0e62d6814/nick-night-RrOtl3HSP80-unsplash.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/dfefa37c-e64f-4ef5-895c-e7f0e62d6814/nick-night-RrOtl3HSP80-unsplash.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class="">Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@nicknight?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Nick Night</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/an-outdoor-cafe-with-tables-and-stools-in-front-of-it-RrOtl3HSP80?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">Budapest is famous for its unique <a href="https://www.google.com/search?sca_esv=0e526ec8824269be&amp;rlz=1C5CHFA_enCA861CA861&amp;sxsrf=ADLYWIIHL-Viw8CD7eGkeotCyV4fijm24g:1722925086121&amp;q=budapest+ruin+bars&amp;spell=1&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwjuju6N3N-HAxWbrYkEHYlPAiQQBSgAegQIERAB&amp;biw=1224&amp;bih=625&amp;dpr=1"><span>ruin bars</span></a>. These are bars set up in abandoned buildings and courtyards, with graffiti &amp; plants that attract visitors from all over the world. These bars offer a quirky atmosphere and affordable drinks, making them a must-visit for anyone on a budget. <a href="https://szimpla.hu/"><span>Szimpla Kert </span></a>is the most well-known ruin bar, but there are <a href="https://ruinbarsbudapest.hu/?utm_source=gmb_ruinpubcrawl&amp;utm_medium=website"><span>many others</span></a> to explore throughout the city.</p><p class="">Entry is free for most of these bars, though some might charge you a cover fee, so be prepared to spend a minimum of 500-2000 HFs - about 1-5 euros or $2-7 CAD / $1-5.50 USD.</p>





















  
  






  <p class="">3. Visit the Great Market Hall</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/363028f5-74ad-4b4c-831f-1bae69d3095f/jacopo-maiarelli--gOUx23DNks-unsplash.jpg" data-image-dimensions="1920x1280" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/363028f5-74ad-4b4c-831f-1bae69d3095f/jacopo-maiarelli--gOUx23DNks-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w" width="1920" height="1280" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/363028f5-74ad-4b4c-831f-1bae69d3095f/jacopo-maiarelli--gOUx23DNks-unsplash.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/363028f5-74ad-4b4c-831f-1bae69d3095f/jacopo-maiarelli--gOUx23DNks-unsplash.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/363028f5-74ad-4b4c-831f-1bae69d3095f/jacopo-maiarelli--gOUx23DNks-unsplash.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/363028f5-74ad-4b4c-831f-1bae69d3095f/jacopo-maiarelli--gOUx23DNks-unsplash.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/363028f5-74ad-4b4c-831f-1bae69d3095f/jacopo-maiarelli--gOUx23DNks-unsplash.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/363028f5-74ad-4b4c-831f-1bae69d3095f/jacopo-maiarelli--gOUx23DNks-unsplash.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/363028f5-74ad-4b4c-831f-1bae69d3095f/jacopo-maiarelli--gOUx23DNks-unsplash.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class="">Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@ja_ma?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Jacopo Maiarelli</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/photos/assorted-fruits-at-the-market--gOUx23DNks?utm_content=creditCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=unsplash">Unsplash</a></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class=""><a href="https://piaconline.hu/nagycsarnok/"><span>The Great Market Hall</span></a>, or Nagyvásárcsarnok, is a vibrant and bustling market where you can experience local culture and cuisine without spending much. It's a great place to sample traditional Hungarian foods, buy fresh produce, and pick up affordable souvenirs. The market also offers a glimpse into daily life in Budapest, making it a rich cultural experience.&nbsp;</p><p class="">As with all markets, it’s absolutely free to visit, so you don’t have to spend any money to have fun while you’re there - as it’s just beautiful to walk around and experience it.&nbsp;</p><p class="">If you’re hungry, it’s also a great place to get affordable and delicious meals for cheap.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Well, travellers? Have I given you enough courage to get back up, go out there, and enjoy Budapest on a budget? </p><p class="">If yes, subscribe to our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/people/Resilience-Routes/61551906447595/" target="_blank">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://x.com/R_Routes" target="_blank">Twitter / X</a>, and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/resilienceroutes/?next=%2F" target="_blank">Instagram</a> channels to get instant, weekly, budget-friendly backpacking and travel tips &amp; tricks like this.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Until next time, have a great one; stay strong, safe, and <strong>resilient </strong>out on your travels.</p>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title>The Frugal Traveler's Guide to Budapest: Must-See Sights and Experiences</title><dc:creator>Michael Boroda</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 23:09:31 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.resilienceroutes.com/blog/the-frugal-travelers-guide-to-budapest-must-see-sights-and-experiences</link><guid isPermaLink="false">64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588:64fce74e086c7e17fabddba4:66a967405745a84555b35d32</guid><description><![CDATA[“Of course it’s not all foie gras and fine wines. There are other 
