  <p class="">If you’re into graffiti art, Tumblingerstraße is a must-visit.&nbsp;</p><p class="">This is an area known for its incredible street art, showcasing the creativity and talent of local and international artists.&nbsp;</p><p class="">It's a great place to take a leisurely walk, get some exercise, and snap some unique photos.&nbsp;</p><p class="">The graffiti is constantly updated so there’s always something new to discover.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Best of all? It’s entirely free - so you don’t have to worry about money.</p><p class="">That about sums it up for this blog post.&nbsp;</p><p class="">If you like our content, consider subscribing to our social media channels on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/people/Resilience-Routes/61551906447595/" target="_blank">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://x.com/R_Routes" target="_blank">Twitter / X</a> and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/resilienceroutes/?next=%2F" target="_blank">Instagram</a> to receive more practical advice on budget backpacking and travel.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Comment below or on our posts in the aforementioned channels to give us <em>your </em>travel insights, and remember to stay resilient out there.&nbsp;</p><p class="">We’ll see you all next week! Wishing you safe and happy travels.&nbsp;</p>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title>Gourmet Adventures on a Budget: Insider Tips on Dining with Points</title><dc:creator>Michael Boroda</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 24 Jun 2024 17:55:34 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.resilienceroutes.com/blog/gourmet-adventures-on-a-budget-insider-tips-on-dining-with-points</link><guid isPermaLink="false">64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588:64fce74e086c7e17fabddba4:6678bc107ee46e536bc4b81f</guid><description><![CDATA[During my backpacking trip across Western Europe in 2019, I learned 
