        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/e735bd74-86e5-4c82-9711-7e468b30241a/IMG_1591.JPG" data-image-dimensions="4032x3024" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/e735bd74-86e5-4c82-9711-7e468b30241a/IMG_1591.JPG?format=1000w" width="4032" height="3024" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/e735bd74-86e5-4c82-9711-7e468b30241a/IMG_1591.JPG?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/e735bd74-86e5-4c82-9711-7e468b30241a/IMG_1591.JPG?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/e735bd74-86e5-4c82-9711-7e468b30241a/IMG_1591.JPG?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/e735bd74-86e5-4c82-9711-7e468b30241a/IMG_1591.JPG?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/e735bd74-86e5-4c82-9711-7e468b30241a/IMG_1591.JPG?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/e735bd74-86e5-4c82-9711-7e468b30241a/IMG_1591.JPG?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/e735bd74-86e5-4c82-9711-7e468b30241a/IMG_1591.JPG?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">This one’s going to sound super obvious, and it’s a must-do activity for anyone visiting Lucerne.&nbsp;</p><p class="">That’s right: take a hike.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Not from this blog post; around Lucerne.&nbsp;</p><p class="">This is one of the best ways to experience the city without spending a single dime - unless of course you want to<a href="#point-three-ice-cream-chocolate" target="_blank"> indulge in chocolate, ice cream</a>, or just some general food.&nbsp;</p><p class="">There is so much to see and experience in this city, and no, a lot of it doesn’t have to cost a lot of money, despite whatever preconceived notions you might have about Switzerland being expensive.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Activities like taking a dip in the supremely warm waters of Lake Lucerne - which you can do even when there’s snow on the mountains, since the actual weather can be quite warm, like when I visited in late May / early June of 2019 -, walking along the <a href="https://www.luzern.com/de/stadt/sehenswuerdigkeiten/top-sehenswuerdigkeiten/kapellbruecke"><span>chapel bridge</span></a> - AKA The Kapellbrücke, built in 1333 - and taking photos of its stunning water tower, flowers, as well as the surrounding lake and village known as Old Town, which has buildings dating back to the 1400s -, walking along <a href="https://www.luzern.com/de/stadt/sehenswuerdigkeiten/top-sehenswuerdigkeiten/spreuerbruecke"><span>Spreuer Bridge</span></a>, and hiking up the steep hill atop Old Town to the medieval <a href="https://www.museggmauer.ch/"><span>Musegg Wall</span></a> - AKA Museggmauer -, a city fortification built in the 13th century, which includes bell &amp; block towers; which you can climb for free.&nbsp;</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
