ing.&nbsp;</p><p class="">There are obviously way more cards out there, and I decided to keep the list short so that you don’t get overloaded with too many options.&nbsp;</p><p class="">That way, it’s easier for you to make a decision and not overthink, which wastes a lot of time.&nbsp;</p><p class="">And time is our most valuable resource, especially when we’re traveling - or making plans to travel - the world.&nbsp;</p><p class="">So make the best use of your time and these credit cards; go out there, and have fun.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Also don’t forget to like us on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/people/Resilience-Routes/61551906447595/" target="_blank">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/R_Routes" target="_blank">Twitter / X</a>, and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/resilienceroutes/?next=%2F" target="_blank">Instagram</a> so that you instantly receive more actionable insights to make you more resilient, and to make saving money on your travels that much easier.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Feel free to comment and suggest your own travel credit cards down below!&nbsp;</p><p class="">Have a great week!&nbsp;</p>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title>Roaming Rome: Budget Backpacking Like a Boss</title><dc:creator>Michael Boroda</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 16 Apr 2024 01:32:56 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.resilienceroutes.com/blog/roaming-rome-budget-backpacking-like-a-boss</link><guid isPermaLink="false">64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588:64fce74e086c7e17fabddba4:661b60eea520311365717f3f</guid><description><![CDATA[“A fool is one who admires other cities without visiting Rome.”

