        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/8d828024-9fdf-445d-ba8e-959c28709ee9/IMG_0687.JPG" data-image-dimensions="4032x3024" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/8d828024-9fdf-445d-ba8e-959c28709ee9/IMG_0687.JPG?format=1000w" width="4032" height="3024" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/8d828024-9fdf-445d-ba8e-959c28709ee9/IMG_0687.JPG?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/8d828024-9fdf-445d-ba8e-959c28709ee9/IMG_0687.JPG?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/8d828024-9fdf-445d-ba8e-959c28709ee9/IMG_0687.JPG?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/8d828024-9fdf-445d-ba8e-959c28709ee9/IMG_0687.JPG?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/8d828024-9fdf-445d-ba8e-959c28709ee9/IMG_0687.JPG?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/8d828024-9fdf-445d-ba8e-959c28709ee9/IMG_0687.JPG?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/8d828024-9fdf-445d-ba8e-959c28709ee9/IMG_0687.JPG?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class="">My first views of the Colosseum.</p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">Thankfully I booked <a href="https://www.coopculture.it/en/tickets/"><span>tickets</span></a> in advance, so I didn’t have to wait in line for more than a few minutes. By the way, you can save money by booking a ticket for the Colosseum and Roman Forum in one, which you might as well do since they’re literally located a one minute walk from one another - so you can just visit one right after the other, which is what I did.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Anyways, getting to the Colosseum early is another way to bypass lines, since even if you book tickets in advance, you’re still susceptible to long wait times if the crowds are large.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Speaking of large crowds, the Colosseum is DEFINITELY a place where you want to be very careful with your valuables, as pickpockets abound here.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Aside from that, you should have a great time here, as you’ll be visiting the world’s largest and oldest amphitheater, built between 72-80 AD.&nbsp;</p><p class="">You can visit on your own, like I did, or take a <a href="https://theromanguy.com/tours/italy/rome?nbt=nb%3Aadwords%3Ag%3A1714153653%3A148584178067%3A646230488310&amp;nb_adtype=&amp;nb_kwd=rome%20tours&amp;nb_ti=kwd-12286851&amp;nb_mi=&amp;nb_pc=&amp;nb_pi=&amp;nb_ppi=&amp;nb_placement=&amp;nb_li_ms=&amp;nb_lp_ms=&amp;nb_fii=&amp;nb_ap=&amp;nb_mt=b&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=Cj0KCQjw5cOwBhCiARIsAJ5njuZ_3e9vI7z9ryusX_PXRz9aD8tk-1vKuAfUIab8CZUjsPyZlfX4UWIaAh01EALw_wcB"><span>guided tour</span></a>, many of which allow you to skype lineups. The Colosseum <a href="https://www.coopculture.it/en/tickets/"><span>website</span></a> even has an option for a video guided tour, and / or a tour with an archaeologist.&nbsp;</p><p class="">The cool thing about taking one of the guided tours is that they give you more insight into the history and significance of the Colosseum, things like facts and stories about the gladiatorial games, the architecture, and the people who once filled these ancient walls.</p><p class="">Still, if like me you choose to save a bit of money and instead go on your own, there are tons of plaques with history / explanations on them throughout the Colosseum, so you’ll still be able to get your money’s worth of history lessons.&nbsp;</p><p class="">As you can imagine, the impressiveness of the Colosseum comes from its size, grandeur, and ancient appearance. You’ll likely stand in awe as you gaze upon the massive stone arches and towering walls of this place, imagine the roar of the crowds and the clash of gladiatorial swords as you explore the arena where combatants once battled it out for glory - as seen in Ridley’s Scott’s <em>Gladiator </em>(2000).&nbsp;</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
