          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p class="">Views of the Colosseum from the Roman Forum. </p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">Now onto the Colosseum’s counterpart…</p>





















  
  






  <p class="">3. Echoes of Empire: Conquer the Majesty of the Roman Forum</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/6ad91720-b6ff-460a-a50f-58d063b791a7/IMG_1099.JPG" data-image-dimensions="4032x3024" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/6ad91720-b6ff-460a-a50f-58d063b791a7/IMG_1099.JPG?format=1000w" width="4032" height="3024" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/6ad91720-b6ff-460a-a50f-58d063b791a7/IMG_1099.JPG?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/6ad91720-b6ff-460a-a50f-58d063b791a7/IMG_1099.JPG?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/6ad91720-b6ff-460a-a50f-58d063b791a7/IMG_1099.JPG?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/6ad91720-b6ff-460a-a50f-58d063b791a7/IMG_1099.JPG?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/6ad91720-b6ff-460a-a50f-58d063b791a7/IMG_1099.JPG?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/6ad91720-b6ff-460a-a50f-58d063b791a7/IMG_1099.JPG?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/6ad91720-b6ff-460a-a50f-58d063b791a7/IMG_1099.JPG?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">Following my visit to the Colosseum, I use my Colosseum / Roman Forum tour ticket to enter the latter. And boy am I astounded - in a GREAT way.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Gentlemen, you know that feeling of disappointment that comes from setting your expectations so high for an experience, that by the time it actually comes to fruition, nothing can live up to it?&nbsp;</p><p class="">Well that feeling does not exist when you visit the Roman Forum.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Much like with <a href="https://www.resilienceroutes.com/blog/neapolitan-adventures-thrills-spills-and-gelato-chills#point-two-pompeii" target="_blank">Pompeii</a>, walking through the Roman Forum is not unlike stepping into a time machine. You literally feel like you’ve been transported into Ancient Roman times, with the gargantuan remnants of the public square and buildings surrounding you - and sometimes towering over you - at every turn.&nbsp;</p><p class="">If you’ve ever seen the Roman Forum depicted in movies, it’s not much less epic in real life. It really <em>is </em>that cool.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Now before diving into the ruins, you’ll want to take a moment to orient yourself at one of the overlooks - so you can see the whole museum from above. From up here, you can get a bird's-eye view of the sprawling site and plan your exploration route, since it’s really up to you what direction you’ll want to take when visiting the square’s ruins - unless you take a <a href="https://www.getyourguide.com/-l2618/?cmp=ga&amp;cq_src=google_ads&amp;cq_cmp=6656466851&amp;cq_con=77193596537&amp;cq_term=tours%20of%20roman%20forum&amp;cq_med=&amp;cq_plac=&amp;cq_net=g&amp;cq_pos=&amp;cq_plt=gp&amp;campaign_id=6656466851&amp;adgroup_id=77193596537&amp;target_id=aud-1393039794940:kwd-36664237050&amp;loc_physical_ms=9000797&amp;match_type=e&amp;ad_id=395195268621&amp;keyword=tours%20of%20roman%20forum&amp;ad_position=&amp;feed_item_id=&amp;placement=&amp;device=c&amp;partner_id=CD951&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=Cj0KCQjwiMmwBhDmARIsABeQ7xSjTqFKheBLtaXC6yCKDEBu0-rHQCkr5QFTFZBDXUfXgzE2D9gusxQaApGvEALw_wcB"><span>guided tour.</span></a>&nbsp;</p><p class="">Speaking of guided tours, it’s not a bad idea to consider joining one led by an expert archaeologist or historian, as they provide invaluable insights into the history and significance of the Forum, allowing you to appreciate the ruins in a deeper context.&nbsp;</p><p class="">While I myself did not take a guided tour and still had a great time, it’s up to you whether or not you feel like it’s worth the investment. If you really like history and love learning about it, then a guide might be worth the price of admission for you.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Now, as you wander through the ancient streets and squares of the Forum, taking in iconic landmarks such as the Temple of Saturn (pictured above), the Arch of Titus, and the Temple of Vesta, you’ll realize that all of these structures tell a story of ancient Roman life and power, dating back to the 7th century B.C.&nbsp;</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
