                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/ab5d47c5-fc6b-47a7-8f28-6df05a9c9b87/IMG_9751.JPG" data-image-dimensions="4032x3024" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/ab5d47c5-fc6b-47a7-8f28-6df05a9c9b87/IMG_9751.JPG?format=1000w" width="4032" height="3024" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/ab5d47c5-fc6b-47a7-8f28-6df05a9c9b87/IMG_9751.JPG?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/ab5d47c5-fc6b-47a7-8f28-6df05a9c9b87/IMG_9751.JPG?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/ab5d47c5-fc6b-47a7-8f28-6df05a9c9b87/IMG_9751.JPG?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/ab5d47c5-fc6b-47a7-8f28-6df05a9c9b87/IMG_9751.JPG?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/ab5d47c5-fc6b-47a7-8f28-6df05a9c9b87/IMG_9751.JPG?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/ab5d47c5-fc6b-47a7-8f28-6df05a9c9b87/IMG_9751.JPG?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/64fce6ab35ce4611b9594588/ab5d47c5-fc6b-47a7-8f28-6df05a9c9b87/IMG_9751.JPG?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">While getting tickets to a guided tour of this place was a pain in the ass - don’t make the mistake that I did and spend an hour arguing with the company that I had to argue with… I wish I could remember their names, and I don’t… anyways -, the actual tour was exceptional - and the tour guide was an absolute mensch; one of the nicest guys I’ve ever met.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Many of you might’ve seen the Vatican in such movies as <em>Angels and Demons</em> (2009),&nbsp; <em>Mission Impossible III </em>(2006)<em>,</em> &amp; <em>John Wick Chapter 2 </em>(2017), and it’s even better than that in person.&nbsp;</p><p class="">I know… Rome has a habit of surpassing expectations when you actually visit it. No wonder it’s called the Eternal City!</p><p class="">Anyways, you obviously want to book <a href="https://www.getyourguide.com/-l2738/?cmp=ga&amp;cq_src=google_ads&amp;cq_cmp=6656469113&amp;cq_con=77344985405&amp;cq_term=vatican%20city%20tickets&amp;cq_med=&amp;cq_plac=&amp;cq_net=g&amp;cq_pos=&amp;cq_plt=gp&amp;campaign_id=6656469113&amp;adgroup_id=77344985405&amp;target_id=aud-1393039794940:kwd-3787017184&amp;loc_physical_ms=9000797&amp;match_type=e&amp;ad_id=394497839660&amp;keyword=vatican%20city%20tickets&amp;ad_position=&amp;feed_item_id=&amp;placement=&amp;device=c&amp;partner_id=CD951&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gclid=Cj0KCQjwiMmwBhDmARIsABeQ7xS7xgkHkgh47hsMVcYC8CP_HGvZRu_zt3cmNNCznuB2ym_Sgxtpx6MaAitrEALw_wcB"><span>tickets</span></a> to Vatican City in advance; arrive as early as possible - depending on your tour times - to beat the crowds and / or to not miss your tour guide - like I almost did.&nbsp;</p><p class="">While you can visit the Vatican on your own, without a tour guide, I highly recommend you go with one, since their knowledge of the grounds as well as the history of each and every art piece is 100% worth the additional cost for the price of admission.&nbsp;</p><p class="">You’re already in Rome, so you might as well get the most out of it, and splurge a little bit on the stuff that matters, with the Vatican being at the forefront of that list.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Your tour guide will likely spend a while taking you through the Vatican Museums - as mine did -, which house one of the most extensive art collections in the world.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Museum highlights include the Raphael Rooms, the Gallery of Maps, and the Sistine Chapel, where you can admire Michelangelo's famous and insanely intricate ceiling frescoes, including the iconic depiction of the Creation of Adam.</p><p class="">Speaking of the Sistine Chapel, you’re going to want to take some time to admire and photograph it, as it’s one of the most famous artistic masterpieces in history.&nbsp;</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
