          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">And last but not least, we have <a href="https://www.orizzonteitalia.com/en/food.2/perche-no!.256"><span>Perché no!...</span></a>, which is considered by many locals - and tourists - to be THE best family owned gelato shop in all of Florence.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Established in 1939, this gelateria - run by the Cammilli family - has a rich heritage that spans generations. In other words, being around for almost a century has caused them to EARN their spot as one of - if not THE top - gelaterias in Florence.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Just like the other places on this list, this gelaterria’s ingredients are fresh &amp; locally sourced; the gelato is handcrafted in small batches to ensure the highest quality of flavors.&nbsp;</p><p class="">It too offers traditional and creative flavors, from seasonal fruit sorbets to decadent chocolate combinations. I’ve heard of people recommending ginger, curry with mango and peaches, Sacher cake, green tea, lavender, and salted caramel flavors in addition to the classical flavors, like pistachio nut, Florentine cream and milk cream with honey and sesame. Whatever suits your taste buds!</p><p class="">Beyond its delicious gelato offerings, Perché no!... is known for its warm and welcoming atmosphere. Whether you're a first-time visitor or a regular patron, you'll be greeted with a smile and treated like family by the friendly staff, who are always happy to help you navigate the menu and find the perfect flavor to satisfy your cravings.</p><p class="">Situated in the heart of Florence's historic center, Perché no!... is located INCREDIBLY close to such landmarks as <a href="https://duomo.firenze.it/it/scopri/cattedrale-di-santa-maria-del-fiore"><span>The Florence Cathedral</span></a>, and the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Piazza_della_Signoria"><span>Piazza della Signoria</span></a>, to name just a few. It’s not only delicious and worth the money and time; it’s also an incredibly convenient location for when you’re exploring the city and its attractions.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Whether you're wandering the cobblestone streets of the city or taking in the sights along the Arno River, Perché no!... provides the perfect pit stop for a refreshing gelato break.</p><p class="">The prices are also really low, with small cups / cones starting as low as €2.70, going up anywhere to €18 if you get really picky. They also offer gluten free options.&nbsp;</p><p class="">In summary, Perché no!... offers a truly authentic gelato experience that celebrates the timeless traditions of Italian craftsmanship, hospitality, and culinary excellence. With its dedication to quality ingredients, artisanal craftsmanship, and warm, welcoming atmosphere, Perché no!... invites you to savor the flavors of Italy and create memories that will last a lifetime.&nbsp;</p><p class="">And it also just tastes really f*****g good.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Alright, guys, that’s it for this blog post.&nbsp;</p><p class="">In case nobody else told you today, we love you and hope you have a great time backpacking.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Gelato is unmissable when you’re in Italy - or really anywhere; Italy specifically, and Florence even more so because that’s where it originated -, and if you plan smartly, you can have it every day without breaking your wallet - I know I did.&nbsp;</p><p class="">If you’re getting something out of these blog posts, and you want more, high-quality insights and hacks on backpacking on a budget, as well as actionable tips and tricks on how to save money while having the adventures of a lifetime, then like us on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/people/Resilience-Routes/61551906447595/" target="_blank">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/i/flow/login?redirect_after_login=%2FR_Routes" target="_blank">Twitter / X</a>, and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/resilienceroutes/?next=%2F" target="_blank">Instagram</a> to get weekly updates on our new articles that’ll help YOU navigate your backpacking travels with ease, fun, and money in your wallet.&nbsp;</p><p class="">Until next time, stay safe, resilient, and have an awesome time out there; we’ll see you all next week.&nbsp;</p>]]></content:encoded></item></channel></rss>